In this parody of crises of sexual orientation, two friends, David (Stuart Perelmuter) and Eric (Brian Gligor) find themselves immersed in the gay community of Louisville, Kentucky when they move from Kansas to live with David\&#039;s aunt. After both join the all-male musical production THE IMPORTANCE OF SINGING EARNEST, Eric finds the confidence to come out as gay, but David, who is straight, finds himself doubting his sexuality. When David finds himself in a predicament with the alluring female stage-manger Lauren and has a hilarious homoerotic nightmare, he decides that he too must be gay, and sets about living the life
